      "description": "The NetBSD Editline library",
      "note": "Changes in libedit 20260508:\n\n- Add a method to set custom wordchars ([59737](http://gnats.netbsd.org/59737))\n- Add `EL_GETENV` to set the function used to fetch environment variables\n- nia: implement `rl_kill_full_line` ([59883](http://gnats.netbsd.org/59883))\n- Fix printing a help message on top of a multiline entry while editing\n- Fix handling of long lines ([60050](http://gnats.netbsd.org/60050))\n- Fix history resizing and copying ([60050](http://gnats.netbsd.org/60050))\n- Fix `history_load` off-by-one memory access bug ([60052](http://gnats.netbsd.org/60052))\n- Adding user-defined functions with narrow name/description leaks memory ([60054](http://gnats.netbsd.org/60054))\n- No need to keep an `allocated` field.  We know that the first `EL_NUM_FCNS` are not allocated.\n- Fix use-after-free in `map_end`\n- Do not assume that chars are 8 bits in `unvis`",
